	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The 245 is buffering the CHR data bus, but it's not immediately apparent what enables the buffer. Perhaps they used a very slow ROM or the ROM has only one enable, so they tied it enabled and the 245 is used for output enable (A13 || /RD). It doesn't really matter,  you don't need it if you used a JEDEC EPROM and tied /OE to /RD and /CE to A13.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
